accepting things on the basis of no evidence. It's believing any old nonsense. It's naive Tay. It's superstition. So, you know, look, I'm for science. I'm not for faith.

00:01:29.280 --> 00:01:30.176
of faith.

00:01:30.848 --> 00:01:34.400
I always want to tear my hair out when I hear a versus event.

00:01:34.336 --> 00:01:36.160
Because that,

00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:40.480
It has nothing to do with what the Bible means by faith.

00:01:40.736 --> 00:01:42.400
Superstition. Superstition.

00:01:42.272 --> 00:01:45.664
A credulity naivete.

00:01:45.440 --> 00:01:49.280
Those are all things that are beneath reason.

00:01:49.760 --> 00:01:59.808
They're shy of reason. They don't reach the level of reason. And the church is against those things. Now, why? Why? Because we believe that Jesus is the Lord.

00:01:59.328 --> 00:02:05.216
He's the Logos. He's the logic. He's the mind of God made flesh, right?

00:02:04.800 --> 00:02:09.024
Therefore, what's illogical is opposed to Christ.

00:02:09.024 --> 00:02:19.072
So please, especially parents, maybe teachers, grandparents listening to me, whenever you hear someone talking about faith that way, just know

00:02:18.592 --> 00:02:25.216
No, automatically have my face and voice appear to you saying, that's not good.

00:02:25.024 --> 00:02:26.880
what we mean by faith.

